---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Accessibility Statement | Lighthouse Mentoring" 
  description="Our commitment to making Lighthouse Mentoring's wellbeing audit services accessible to everyone."
>
  <section class="hero-gradient py-20">
    <div class="container px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-navy-900 mb-4">
          Accessibility Statement
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700">
          Making wellbeing support accessible to everyone
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mb-8">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</p>
        
        <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
        <p>
          Lighthouse Mentoring is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying relevant accessibility standards.
        </p>

        <h2>Accessibility Standards</h2>
        <p>
          We aim to conform to the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA standards. These guidelines help make web content more accessible to people with various disabilities including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Visual impairments</li>
          <li>Hearing impairments</li>
          <li>Motor impairments</li>
          <li>Cognitive disabilities</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
        <h3>Website Features</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Clear and consistent navigation structure</li>
          <li>Descriptive alt text for images</li>
          <li>Sufficient color contrast for text and backgrounds (WCAG AA compliant)</li>
          <li>Keyboard navigation support throughout the site</li>
          <li>Semantic HTML for better screen reader compatibility</li>
          <li>Responsive design for various devices and screen sizes</li>
          <li>Skip links for keyboard navigation</li>
          <li>Focus indicators for interactive elements</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Survey Accessibility</h3>
        <p>
          Our wellbeing surveys are designed to be accessible:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Clear, simple language in all questions</li>
          <li>Alternative formats available upon request</li>
          <li>Extended time allowances when needed</li>
          <li>Compatible with assistive technologies</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Known Limitations</h2>
        <p>
          While we strive for full accessibility, some areas may have limitations:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Some third-party content may not meet all accessibility standards</li>
          <li>Older PDF documents may not be fully accessible (we're working to update these)</li>
          <li>Complex data visualizations may require alternative text descriptions</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Alternative Formats</h2>
        <p>
          We can provide information in alternative formats including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Large print documents</li>
          <li>Audio recordings</li>
          <li>Easy-read versions</li>
          <li>Alternative survey formats</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Please <a href="/contact/" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-800">contact us</a> to request alternative formats.
        </p>

        <h2>Feedback and Contact</h2>
        <p>
          We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website and services. Please let us know if you encounter accessibility barriers:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Email: accessibility@lighthousementoring.co.uk</li>
          <li>Phone: Available upon request</li>
          <li><a href="/contact/" class="text-teal-700 hover:text-teal-800">Contact Form</a></li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          We try to respond to accessibility feedback within 2 business days and will work to resolve issues promptly.
        </p>

        <h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
        <p>
          This website is built using modern web technologies with accessibility in mind:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Semantic HTML5</li>
          <li>ARIA labels where appropriate</li>
          <li>CSS for presentation</li>
          <li>Progressive enhancement approach</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Browser Compatibility</h2>
        <p>
          Our website is tested and compatible with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Latest versions of Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge</li>
          <li>Screen readers including JAWS, NVDA, and VoiceOver</li>
          <li>Voice recognition software</li>
          <li>Keyboard-only navigation</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Continuous Improvement</h2>
        <p>
          We view accessibility as an ongoing effort and regularly:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Review and test our website for accessibility</li>
          <li>Train our team on accessibility best practices</li>
          <li>Update our content and design based on user feedback</li>
          <li>Monitor accessibility standards and guidelines</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Legal Compliance</h2>
        <p>
          This website strives to comply with:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Equality Act 2010</li>
          <li>Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) Accessibility Regulations 2018</li>
          <li>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-navy-900 mb-4">
          Need Assistance?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          We're here to help make our services accessible to you.
        </p>
        <Button href="/contact/" variant="primary">
          Get in Touch
        </Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>